ully spawned, there are generally 4 or 5 mobs in there...the last several times I've been through courtyard, there have been undead in the corners and golems in the middle...don't know if this it typical spawn or not.<br><br>However, the last several times, I've been able to go invis and walk right through the middle of the room (tickling the toes on the golems) without aggroing the undead.<br><br>On the other side of the courtyard is a hallway that goes left and right.  Follow the hall right and you'll come out into an open area with plants, partially paved, partially grass.  Go to the east wall here, along the paved area.  Face west and there's a building in the center of this &quot;courtyard&quot;, with a door facing you.<br><br>This building is the &quot;Goo House&quot;.  Open the door, and there is a small set of stairs going down.  In the center of the room is the primary Goo spawn, and there are several up on the ledge to the left.<br><br>I generally pull with IC from the doorway, big bang and cast time doesn't matter because you're not getting beat on yet.   I then back up back to the wall, and then standard root/nuke from there.<br><br>You can kite in this hallway, but I tend not to because I like big open areas that I can run straight in when I kite.  If you choose to kite, root the sucker then snare him so you don't get caught in AE radius of Atols/BoF, or just pull the single with your snare.<br><br>I go straight root/nuke here however, with skin up.  One of the goos does hit hard...doubles for 120.  I've not had a root/nuke go bad here tho.<br><br>At 55 with 227 int and about 450 extra mana, I go to about 2 blue on a root/nuke.  <br><br>One important note.  Nothing wanders through this courtyard where you're sitting.  However, you *will* see ghosts wander right over you...ignore them, they're not really there.  If you do target/cast on them, you're probably going to end up in a very bad way.  Just let them go about their business, and you go about yours, and you'll both (all?) be happier in the long run.<br><br>Shizz<br> <p>Shizza Nidiot54th Companion to the Chetari Rats of Dragon NecropolisQueen of the Goblin Pulls</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ubenton666.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Benton666</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/25/02 9:53:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=340.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Soloing in CoM</span><hr size=1> Thanks a lot... I also heard that there is a place to solo in Neriak Foreign Quater.  I pulled Jacker, killed him easy, went to go find others and I found this house with about 5 blue troll/ogres.  I went to a beastiary site that has level info and most of them are lvl 50.  Is there any way to solo pull them at all? <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showPrevMessage?topicID=340.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showNextMessage?topicID=340.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=340.topic&index=2><img src=http://www.graffe.com/messageboard/add_reply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm19.emailToFriend?topicID=340.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompila